The paper deals with algorithms for the sliding-window model, which is a variant of the data-stream model. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also deals with graph streams and graph problems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. The paper uses the smooth histogram framework, which is a technique for reducing the sliding-window model to the insertion-only streaming model, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with subadditive functions, which are a type of function that satisfies a certain property, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.AL (Algorithms) sub-category.
